According to reports from the scene, the 32-year-old tourist had slipped and fell about eight metres. CAPE TOWN - A tourist has fallen on Table Mountain.Netcare 911 says paramedics were dispatched before noon to assist a woman who fell on Lion's Head.According to reports from the scene, the 32-year-old tourist had slipped and fell about eight metres.Netcare 911's Chris Botha said: &quot;The paramedics, as well as the rescue unit and Cape Wildlife officials, were on the mountain. They assisted us in getting the patient back down to where the ambulance was.&quot;The woman was taken to hospital.No further details were made available.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)